    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Seven-bit code used in computing to store and transmit standard English language characters, punctuation, and numerals. It was developed by the American National Standards Institute and is used in most personal computers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
